Package edu.ncsu.csc216.stp.model.manager

Class TestPlanManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.stp.model.manager.TestPlanManager
  • public class TestPlanManager
extends java.lang.Object
    A TestPlanManager has an ISortedList of TestPlans, one FailingTestList, an AbstractTestPlan for the currentTestPlan, and a boolean flag that keeps track of if the TestPlanManager has been changed since the last save.
    Author:
    Mari Kilgus, Bagya Maharajan

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor Description
      TestPlanManager()
      The testPlans field is constructed as a SortedList and the failingTestList is constructed and is set as the currentTestPlan.

    • Constructor Detail

      • TestPlanManager

        public TestPlanManager()
        The testPlans field is constructed as a SortedList and the failingTestList is constructed and is set as the currentTestPlan. isChanged is initialized to false. The clearTestPlans() method can be helpful for completing these tasks.

    • Method Detail

      • loadTestPlans

        public void loadTestPlans​(java.io.File testPlanFile)
        The TestPlanReader is used to load the file and return a list of potential TestPlans to add to the list of TestPlans. If there is already a TestPlan in the testPlans with the given name, the incoming TestPlan is not added (remember SortedList already checks for duplicates!). After loading all the new TestPlans (or not), the currentTestPlan is set to the Failing Tests list. This should be done using setCurrentTestPlan().
        Parameters:
        testPlanFile - the file parameter to load

      • saveTestPlans

        public void saveTestPlans​(java.io.File testPlanFile)
        Saves the current TestPlans to the given file. isChanged is updated to false.
        Parameters:
        testPlanFile - the file parameter to save

      • isChanged

        public boolean isChanged()
        keeps track of if the TestPlanManager has been changed since the last save.
        Returns:
        true if TestPlanManager has been changed since the last save

      • addTestPlan

        public void addTestPlan​(java.lang.String testPlanName)
        If the new TestPlan’s name is FAILING_TESTS_LIST_NAME or a duplicate of an existing TestPlan (both case insensitive), then an IAE is thrown with message "Invalid name." Otherwise, the TestPlan is added to the list of test plans, the current test plan is updated to the new test plan (use setCurrentTestPlan()), and isChanged is updated to true. Where possible delegate to other methods for error checking.
        Parameters:
        testPlanName - the name of the test plan to be added
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the new TestPlan’s name is FAILING_TESTS_LIST_NAME or a duplicate of an existing TestPlan (both case insensitive)

      • getTestPlanNames

        public java.lang.String[] getTestPlanNames()
        Returns a list of test plan names. The Failing Tests list is always listed first.
        Returns:
        a list of test plan names

      • setCurrentTestPlan

        public void setCurrentTestPlan​(java.lang.String testPlanName)
        Sets the currentTestPlan to the AbstractTestPlan with the given name. If a TestPlan with that name is not found, then the currentTestPlan is set to the failingTestList (don't forget to update the failingTestList first!).
        Parameters:
        testPlanName - the name of the current test plan to set

      • getCurrentTestPlan

        public AbstractTestPlan getCurrentTestPlan()
        Gets the current test plan
        Returns:
        an AbstractTestPlan object representing the current test plan

      • editTestPlan

        public void editTestPlan​(java.lang.String testPlanName)
        An IAE is thrown if the currentTestPlan is an FailingTestList (message “The Failing Tests list may not be edited.), if the new name matches “Failing Tests (case insensitive) (message “Invalid name.), or is a duplicate of the name of another TestPlan (case insensitive and including if the name is the same as the list that will be renamed) (message “Invalid name.). Note that when editing, you are editing the currentTestPlan and you cannot edit the TestPlan in place in the ISortedList. You must maintain sorted order (i.e., remove, edit, add). isChanged is updated to true.
        Parameters:
        testPlanName - the name of the test plan to edit
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if currentTestPlan is in the FailingTestList the new name matches “Failing Tests (case insensitive) (message “Invalid name.), or is a duplicate of the name of another TestPlan (case insensitive and including if the name is the same as the list that will be renamed) (message “Invalid name.)

      • removeTestPlan

        public void removeTestPlan()
        An IAE is thrown if the currentTestPlan is an FailingTestList with the message “The Failing Tests list may not be deleted. Otherwise, the currentTestPlan is removed and then set to the failingTestList. isChanged is updated to true.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the currentTestPlan is an FailingTestList with the message “The Failing Tests list may not be deleted.

      • addTestCase

        public void addTestCase​(TestCase t)
        A TestCase can only be added directly to a TestPlan. If the currentTestPlan is not a TestPlan do nothing with the TestCase. If the currentTestPlan is a TestPlan, then add the test case and check if the TestCase is failing. If so, then you can update the failingTestList. This is a place where the helper method getFailingTests() can be helpful. isChanged is updated to true.
        Parameters:
        t - the test case to add

      • addTestResult

        public void addTestResult​(int idx,
                          boolean passing,
                          java.lang.String actualResult)
        Adds the test result to the test case at the given index in the current test plan. If the tests are failing, then the Failing Test List should be updated.
        Parameters:
        idx - the idx to add at
        passing - whether it is passing
        actualResult - the actual result of the test

      • clearTestPlans

        public void clearTestPlans()
        Clears out the TestPlanManager by setting testPlans to an empty SortedList, failingTestList to an empty FailingTestList(), currentTestPlan to the failingTestList, and isChanged to false.
